### Task 3: Implement countBeamCells\n   168→\n   169→**Files:**\n   170→- Modify: `src/index.ts`\n   171→\n   172→**Dependencies:** Task 2\n   173→\n   174→**Step 1: Implement helper types, findSource, traceBeam, and countBeamCells**\n   175→\n   176→```typescript\n   177→type Direction = 'down' | 'down-left' | 'down-right';\n   178→\n   179→const DELTAS: Record<Direction, [number, number]> = {\n   180→  'down': [1, 0],\n   181→  'down-left': [1, -1],\n   182→  'down-right': [1, 1],\n   183→};\n   184→\n   185→function findSource(grid: string[][]): [number, number] {\n   186→  for (let col = 0; col < grid[0].length; col++) {\n   187→    if (grid[0][col] === 'S') return [0, col];\n   188→  }\n   189→  throw new Error('No source found');\n   190→}\n   191→\n   192→interface TraceResult {\n   193→  visitedCells: [number, number][];\n   194→  hitSplitter: [number, number] | null;\n   195→}\n   196→\n   197→function traceBeam(\n   198→  grid: string[][],\n   199→  startRow: number,\n   200→  startCol: number,\n   201→  dir: Direction,\n   202→): TraceResult {\n   203→  const rows = grid.length;\n   204→  const cols = grid[0].length;\n   205→  const [dRow, dCol] = DELTAS[dir];\n   206→  const visited: [number, number][] = [];\n   207→\n   208→  let r = startRow;\n   209→  let c = startCol;\n   210→\n   211→  while (r >= 0 && r < rows && c >= 0 && c < cols) {\n   212→    visited.push([r, c]);\n   213→    if (grid[r][c] === '^' && (r !== startRow || c !== startCol)) {\n   214→      return { visitedCells: visited, hitSplitter: [r, c] };\n   215→    }\n   216→    r += dRow;\n   217→    c += dCol;\n   218→  }\n   219→\n   220→  return { visitedCells: visited, hitSplitter: null };\n   221→}\n   222→\n   223→export function countBeamCells(grid: string[][]): number {\n   224→  const [sRow, sCol] = findSource(grid);\n   225→  const visited = new Set<string>();\n   226→  visited.add(`${sRow},${sCol}`);\n   227→\n   228→  // BFS through splitter graph\n   229→  // Start: trace beam down from source position (from the cell below source)\n   230→  const queue: Array<{ row: number; col: number; dir: Direction }> = [];\n   231→\n   232→  // Initial beam goes down from source\n   233→  const initResult = traceBeam(grid, sRow + 1, sCol, 'down');\n   234→  for (const [r, c] of initResult.visitedCells) {\n   235→    visited.add(`${r},${c}`);\n   236→  }\n   237→  if (initResult.hitSplitter) {\n   238→    queue.push({ row: initResult.hitSplitter[0], col: initResult.hitSplitter[1], dir: 'down' });\n   239→  }\n   240→\n   241→  // Track processed splitters to avoid reprocessing\n   242→  const processedSplitters = new Set<string>();\n   243→\n   244→  while (queue.length > 0) {\n   245→    const { row, col } = queue.shift()!;\n   246→    const key = `${row},${col}`;\n   247→    if (processedSplitters.has(key)) continue;\n   248→    processedSplitters.add(key);\n   249→\n   250→    // Splitter emits down-left and down-right from the next cells\n   251→    for (const dir of ['down-left', 'down-right'] as Direction[]) {\n   252→      const [dRow, dCol] = DELTAS[dir];\n   253→      const nextRow = row + dRow;\n   254→      const nextCol = col + dCol;\n   255→      const result = traceBeam(grid, nextRow, nextCol, dir);\n   256→      for (const [r, c] of result.visitedCells) {\n   257→        visited.add(`${r},${c}`);\n   258→      }\n   259→      if (result.hitSplitter) {\n   260→        queue.push({ row: result.hitSplitter[0], col: result.hitSplitter[1], dir });\n   261→      }\n   262→    }\n   263→  }\n   264→\n   265→  return visited.size;\n   266→}\n   267→```\n   268→\n   269→Wait — there's a subtlety. The `traceBeam` function starts at `startRow, startCol` and the first cell it checks could itself be a splitter. But we only want to stop at a splitter that's NOT the starting position (since the starting position is the splitter we're tracing FROM). However, the initial beam from the source starts at `(sRow+1, sCol)` which is the first cell below the source — this cell could be a splitter.\n   270→\n   271→Let me reconsider: `traceBeam` should start from a given position and trace in a direction. The starting position of the trace is the first cell the beam enters AFTER leaving its origin (source or previous splitter). So we check each cell: if it's a splitter, we stop and record it. We need to handle the case where the very first cell of a trace is a splitter.\n   272→\n   273→Revised `traceBeam`: Remove the \"skip starting position\" logic. The beam starts at `(startRow, startCol)` and if that cell is a splitter, it immediately hits it.\n   274→\n   275→```typescript\n   276→function traceBeam(\n   277→  grid: string[][],\n   278→  startRow: number,\n   279→  startCol: number,\n   280→  dir: Direction,\n   281→): TraceResult {\n   282→  const rows = grid.length;\n   283→  const cols = grid[0].length;\n   284→  const [dRow, dCol] = DELTAS[dir];\n   285→  const visited: [number, number][] = [];\n   286→\n   287→  let r = startRow;\n   288→  let c = startCol;\n   289→\n   290→  while (r >= 0 && r < rows && c >= 0 && c < cols) {\n   291→    visited.push([r, c]);\n   292→    if (grid[r][c] === '^') {\n   293→      return { visitedCells: visited, hitSplitter: [r, c] };\n   294→    }\n   295→    r += dRow;\n   296→    c += dCol;\n   297→  }\n   298→\n   299→  return { visitedCells: visited, hitSplitter: null };\n   300→}\n   301→```\n   302→\n   303→And the caller for `countBeamCells` traces from `(sRow + 1, sCol)` with direction `'down'` for the initial beam after the source. Splitters then trace from `(row + dRow, col + dCol)` for each outgoing direction.\n   304→\n   305→**Step 2: Run tests**\n   306→\n   307→Run: `npm test`\n   308→Expected: All countBeamCells tests pass.\n   309→\n   310→**Step 3: Run build and lint**\n   311→\n   312→Run: `npm run build && npm run lint`\n   313→Expected: No errors.\n   314→\n   315→**Step 4: Commit**\n   316→\n   317→```bash\n   318→git add src/index.ts\n   319→git commit -m \"feat: implement countBeamCells with splitter-graph BFS\"\n   320→```\n   321→\n   322→---\n   323→\n   324→### Task 4: Write Tests for countBeamPaths\n   325→\n   326→**Files:**\n   327→- Modify: `tests/index.test.ts`\n   328→\n   329→**Dependencies:** Task 3\n   330→\n   331→**Step 1: Add countBeamPaths test cases**\n   332→\n   333→```typescript\n   334→describe('countBeamPaths', () => {\n   335→  it('no splitters — single path straight down', () => {\n   336→    const grid = [\n   337→      ['.', 'S', '.'],\n   338→      ['.', '.', '.'],\n   339→      ['.', '.', '.'],\n   340→    ];\n   341→    expect(countBeamPaths(grid)).toBe(1n);\n   342→  });\n   343→\n   344→  it('example 1: one splitter → 2 paths', () => {\n   345→    const grid = [\n   346→      ['.', 'S', '.', '.', '.'],\n   347→      ['.', '.', '.', '.', '.'],\n   348→      ['.', '^', '.', '.', '.'],\n   349→      ['.', '.', '.', '.', '.'],\n   350→    ];\n   351→    expect(countBeamPaths(grid)).toBe(2n);\n   352→  });\n   353→\n   354→  it('example 2: three splitters → 4 paths', () => {\n   355→    const grid = [\n   356→      ['.', 'S', '.', '.', '.'],\n   357→      ['.', '^', '.', '.', '.'],\n   358→      ['^', '.', '^', '.', '.'],\n   359→      ['.', '.', '.', '.', '.'],\n   360→    ];\n   361→    expect(countBeamPaths(grid)).toBe(4n);\n   362→  });\n   363→\n   364→  it('single row grid — 1 path (exits immediately)', () => {\n   365→    const grid = [['S']];\n   366→    expect(countBeamPaths(grid)).toBe(1n);\n   367→  });\n   368→\n   369→  it('source at edge with splitter — one path absorbed sideways', () => {\n   370→    const grid = [\n   371→      ['S', '.', '.'],\n   372→      ['^', '.', '.'],\n   373→      ['.', '.', '.'],\n   374→    ];\n   375→    // Splitter at (1,0): down-left goes to (2,-1) exits, down-right goes to (2,1) exits\n   376→    // Both exit = 2 paths\n   377→    expect(countBeamPaths(grid)).toBe(2n);\n   378→  });\n   379→\n   380→  it('chain of splitters — exponential paths', () => {\n   381→    // S at col 4, splitters arranged so each splits into two that each hit another splitter\n   382→    const grid = [\n   383→      ['.', '.', '.', '.', 'S', '.', '.', '.', '.'],\n   384→      ['.', '.', '.', '.', '^', '.', '.', '.', '.'],\n   385→      ['.', '.', '.', '^', '.', '^', '.', '.', '.'],\n   386→      ['.', '.', '^', '.', '.', '.', '^', '.', '.'],\n   387→      ['.', '.', '.', '.', '.', '.', '.', '.', '.'],\n   388→    ];\n   389→    // S(0,4) → (1,4) splitter → (2,3) splitter + (2,5) splitter\n   390→    // (2,3) splitter → (3,2) splitter + (3,4) exits\n   391→    // (2,5) splitter → (3,4) exits + (3,6) splitter\n   392→    // (3,2) splitter → (4,1) + (4,3) = 2 paths\n   393→    // (3,6) splitter → (4,5) + (4,7) = 2 paths\n   394→    // Total: 2 + 1 + 1 + 2 = 6 paths\n   395→    expect(countBeamPaths(grid)).toBe(6n);\n   396→  });\n   397→\n   398→  it('diamond pattern — same splitter reachable from multiple parents', () => {\n   399→    const grid = [\n   400→      ['.', '.', 'S', '.', '.'],\n   401→      ['.', '.', '^', '.', '.'],\n   402→      ['.', '^', '.', '^', '.'],\n   403→      ['.', '.', '^', '.', '.'],\n   404→      ['.', '.', '.', '.', '.'],\n   405→    ];\n   406→    // S(0,2) → (1,2) split\n   407→    // Left: (2,1) split → (3,0) exit + (3,2) split\n   408→    // Right: (2,3) split → (3,2) split + (3,4) exit\n   409→    // (3,2) reached from both (2,1) and (2,3)\n   410→    // (3,2) split → (4,1) exit + (4,3) exit = 2 paths from this splitter\n   411→    // From (2,1): 1 (exit at (3,0)) + 2 (through (3,2)) = 3\n   412→    // From (2,3): 2 (through (3,2)) + 1 (exit at (3,4)) = 3\n   413→    // Total: 3 + 3 = 6\n   414→    expect(countBeamPaths(grid)).toBe(6n);\n   415→  });\n   416→});\n   417→```\n   418→\n   419→**Step 2: Run tests to verify countBeamPaths tests fail**\n   420→\n   421→Run: `npm test`\n   422→Expected: countBeamCells tests pass, countBeamPaths tests fail with \"Not implemented\".\n   423→\n   424→**Step 3: Commit**\n   425→\n   426→```bash\n   427→git add tests/index.test.ts\n   428→git commit -m \"test: add countBeamPaths test cases\"\n   429→```\n   430→\n   431→---\n   432→\n   433→### Task 5: Implement countBeamPaths\n   434→\n   435→**Files:**\n   436→- Modify: `src/index.ts`\n   437→\n   438→**Dependencies:** Task 4\n   439→\n   440→**Step 1: Implement countBeamPaths using memoized DP**\n   441→\n   442→Add a helper `traceBeamTarget` that traces from a position/direction and returns only whether it hit a splitter (and which one) or exited, without collecting cells. Then implement the DP:\n   443→\n   444→```typescript\n   445→interface BeamTarget {\n   446→  hitSplitter: [number, number] | null;  // null means exits grid\n   447→}\n   448→\n   449→function traceBeamTarget(\n   450→  grid: string[][],\n   451→  startRow: number,\n   452→  startCol: number,\n   453→  dir: Direction,\n   454→): BeamTarget {\n   455→  const rows = grid.length;\n   456→  const cols = grid[0].length;\n   457→  const [dRow, dCol] = DELTAS[dir];\n   458→\n   459→  let r = startRow;\n   460→  let c = startCol;\n   461→\n   462→  while (r >= 0 && r < rows && c >= 0 && c < cols) {\n   463→    if (grid[r][c] === '^') {\n   464→      return { hitSplitter: [r, c] };\n   465→    }\n   466→    r += dRow;\n   467→    c += dCol;\n   468→  }\n   469→\n   470→  return { hitSplitter: null };\n   471→}\n   472→\n   473→export function countBeamPaths(grid: string[][]): bigint {\n   474→  if (grid.length <= 1) return 1n;\n   475→\n   476→  const [sRow, sCol] = findSource(grid);\n   477→  const memo = new Map<string, bigint>();\n   478→\n   479→  function pathsFrom(row: number, col: number): bigint {\n   480→    const key = `${row},${col}`;\n   481→    if (memo.has(key)) return memo.get(key)!;\n   482→\n   483→    let total = 0n;\n   484→\n   485→    for (const dir of ['down-left', 'down-right'] as Direction[]) {\n   486→      const [dRow, dCol] = DELTAS[dir];\n   487→      const target = traceBeamTarget(grid, row + dRow, col + dCol, dir);\n   488→      if (target.hitSplitter) {\n   489→        total += pathsFrom(target.hitSplitter[0], target.hitSplitter[1]);\n   490→      } else {\n   491→        total += 1n;  // beam exits grid = one complete path\n   492→      }\n   493→    }\n   494→\n   495→    memo.set(key, total);\n   496→    return total;\n   497→  }\n   498→\n   499→  // Trace initial beam down from source\n   500→  const initTarget = traceBeamTarget(grid, sRow + 1, sCol, 'down');\n   501→  if (initTarget.hitSplitter) {\n   502→    return pathsFrom(initTarget.hitSplitter[0], initTarget.hitSplitter[1]);\n   503→  }\n   504→  return 1n;  // beam exits without hitting any splitter\n   505→}\n   506→```\n   507→\n   508→**Step 2: Run all tests**\n   509→\n   510→Run: `npm test`\n   511→Expected: All tests pass.\n   512→\n   513→**Step 3: Run build and lint**\n   514→\n   515→Run: `npm run build && npm run lint`\n   516→Expected: No errors.\n   517→\n   518→**Step 4: Commit**\n   519→\n   520→```bash\n   521→git add src/index.ts\n   522→git commit -m \"feat: implement countBeamPaths with memoized DP on splitter graph\"\n   523→```\n   524→\n   525→---\n   526→\n   527→### Task 6: Performance Test and Edge Cases\n   528→\n   529→**Files:**\n   530→- Modify: `tests/index.test.ts`\n   531→\n   532→**Dependencies:** Task 5\n   533→\n   534→**Step 1: Add performance test for large grid**\n   535→\n   536→```typescript\n   537→describe('performance', () => {\n   538→  it('200x200 grid with 50 splitters completes in under 5 seconds', () => {\n   539→    const rows = 200;\n   540→    const cols = 200;\n   541→    const grid: string[][] = Array.from({ length: rows }, () =>\n   542→      Array.from({ length: cols }, () => '.')\n   543→    );\n   544→\n   545→    // Place source\n   546→    grid[0][100] = 'S';\n   547→\n   548→    // Place 50 splitters in a binary tree pattern\n   549→    // Each splitter at row r, col c sends beams to (r+1, c-1) and (r+1, c+1)\n   55